OL,3,CGuernsey fisherman concerned about
OL,4,Cfalling numbers of local crabs
OL,6,FShellfish traders on the island are
OL,7,Fnow finding it increasingly difficult
OL,8,Fto meet the demand for brown crab but
OL,9,Fsay there is no shortage of other fish
OL,10,Fand crustaceans they can sell.
OL,12,FJason Hamon, a local fishmonger, said:
OL,13,F"There are plenty of lobsters around
OL,14,Fso we've resorted to picked lobsters
OL,15,Frather than selling picked crab.
OL,17,F"There are always plenty of other fish
OL,18,Fto sell, even the octopus which seems
OL,19,Fto be getting the blame for taking all
OL,20,Fthe crabs."
