OL,3,CGuernsey fisherman concerned about
OL,4,Cfalling numbers of local crabs
OL,6,FThere have been efforts to protect
OL,7,Fmarine species like the brown crab
OL,8,Ffrom overfishing in the Channel
OL,9,FIslands, including Jersey's Marine
OL,10,FSpatial Plan, although global
OL,11,Fenvironmental factors like rising sea
OL,12,Ftemperatures mean it may be unlikely
OL,13,Fthat brown crab numbers will return to
OL,14,Fprevious levels.
OL,16,FBrown crabs prefer to live in cooler
OL,17,Fwaters and rarely live in seas
OL,18,Freaching 20C.
